post_text:
YOU DID IT! üéì It's time to celebrate the fourteen esteemed graduates of Princeton High School's Class of 2020. The Princeton Joint Unified School District Board has voted to host a drive-in graduation ceremony to comprehensively honor the accomplishments of our graduates while complying with the recommendations of the Colusa County Health and Human Services Department.

The Colusa County Public Health Officer is requiring a minimum of six feet between vehicles, with each vehicle containing only members of the same household. Attendees are required to stay in their vehicles for the entire program and public restrooms will not be available. In addition, any in-person congregation of students, staff, and family members before and after the drive-in event will not be permitted.

post_text:
Congratulations to the 5th/6th grade Student of the Trimester, Jaidyn!

Ms. Stegall shares, "Jaidyn is kind to everyone and always shows up to school with a positive attitude. She is honest and trustworthy. Jaidyn often participates during class and works hard in all subjects. She is an awesome writer and writes great stories that are always interesting. Jaidyn is a friend to everyone and sticks up for others. She constantly displays good citizenship and makes our classroom a brighter place. Jaidyn has a great sense of humor and knows how to put a smile on our face. Keep up the good work!"

post_text:
Congratulations to the 3rd/4th grade Student of the Trimester, Cristian!

Mrs. Pierce writes, "My student of the trimester award is going to a young person who is a great all around student. Cristian is polite, raises his hand in class, and works well with all classmates and peers. He is kind, participates in classroom discussions, and has emerged from his shell with regards to sharing and engaging in the classroom. Cristian accepts constructive criticism with his writing and has made goals for the next trimester. He has made goals for this year to include reading more books and taking AR Renaissance tests to increase his comprehension. I enjoy having Cristian in class, and I am impressed with his willingness to reflect on his work and make goals to achieve higher learning. He is friendly, with a cooperative attitude, and is a pleasant addition to our class."

post_text:
Congratulations to the TK/K Student of the Trimester, Isaac!

Mrs. Stillwell writes, "What a delight he is to have in class. Isaac is attentive, extremely kind, helpful, loving, and always cheerful. He listens so well to directions that he rarely needs help. Isaac is kind to every other student in class. He does an excellent job at following the classroom rules and has received many Soaring Eagles to place on our Kindness Tree. Isaac did not know his sounds when the year began and now knows all letters and sounds. He had trouble holding a pencil and writing and now has very nice handwriting. I also get many, many hugs from him each day. It is a joy to teach Isaac!"

NOW HIRING! Custodian/Van Driver

The Custodian/Van Driver will perform a variety of duties at the Jr./Sr. High School under the general supervision of the Director of Maintenance and Operations. Duties include, but are not limited to, facility sweeping, mopping, vacuuming, washing windows, sanitizing tables, desktops and restrooms, stripping and waxing floors, cleaning carpets, assist in the maintenance of gym floors. Position also will drive an evening route with students using a school van and maintain a cooperative working relationship with supervisors, students, community, teachers, administrators and co-workers.

Salary: $13.25-$20.56 per hour (includes longevity)
Hours: 5.5 per day
Days per Year: 180
Benefits: Pro-rated $10,800 Health and Wellness Cap

Required to apply: 3 letters of reference, application, current DMV printout.

Will be subject to pre-employment drug screening and TB test.

Go to Edjoin.org for application, or stop by the district office.

Interview Date: TBA
Hire Date: ASAP

üéâ Congratulations to the 3rd/4th Grade Student of the Trimester, Daniela!

Mrs. Pierce writes, ‚ÄúDaniela is a dedicated student who puts 100% of her efforts into being an engaged student in all ways. She raises her hand during class discussions, has wonderful ideas to share, and is always on topic. She always has amazing ideas to contribute and keeps discussions on topic. When working on science experiments, she goes above and beyond, making projects that are challenging, complete, and clear. She also approaches challenges well and has a good attitude toward school assignments. She has stepped out of her comfort zone and participated in activities beyond the regular school day. I know she is role model to other students, and a great addition to Princeton Elementary School. Keep up the hard work. I am so proud of Daniela. post_text:
ATTENTION SENIORS!

Late registration for the last SAT Exam of the summer is August 13th.

If you plan on applying to a four year university in the fall then you need to have an SAT score. Not having a valid score by the beginning of the application process can move you back in the line of possible new enrollees. This can jeopardize your chances of being admitted to your target college. You will need to create an online College Board account to sign up for the test since it will be a late registration. It can only be done online (including payment).

https://collegereadiness.collegeboard.org/sat/register/august-2019

Seniors and Parents of Seniors
Tuesday 1/29 at 9:00 am in the Career Center a Herff Jones Sales Representative is scheduled for students & Parents to Purchase Graduation Cap & Gown, 2019 Tassel, Class Ring and other Graduation Supplies direct from the manufacturer. Sales brochures will be available for students to take home to parents. Graduation supplies are only available for purchase through Herff Jones. This year the School Board approved students to decorate their Graduation Cap with prior "design pre-approval ." Students who want to decorate their cap will need to purchase their own graduation cap on 1/29. PJUSD will continue to offer a "Loan" of graduation Cap, Gown and Tassel for students for the graduation ceremony.

Yecenia

post_text: Seniors, Isabel, Michelle, Angie, Fiorella and Alysha visited the Veterinary Tech program at Yuba College as a career exploration opportunity on Oct. 29th along with their school Counselor Ms. Robinson. These 5 seniors are deciding careers in the medical profession and are looking into which career pathways to choose. The Princeton Jr./Sr. High students were able to observe surgery procedures involving the spay and neuter clinic of animals from the Oroville Humane Society performed by the Yuba College Veterinarian and 2nd year Vet Tech students.

post_text: Princeton Joint Unified celebrated National Red Ribbon Week Oct 22-26th. Students are holding up Certificates provided by Assemblyman 3rd District,James Gallagher for Princeton Elementary students in grades 2nd - 6th. Princeton Jr./Sr. High School Friday Night Live club members provided face painting for the elementary students in celebration of their pledge to live a "Safe, Healthy and Drug Free Life."
